for bettin' on my hometown ball team.

67
00:04:41,115 --> 00:04:43,116
I ought to have better sense.

68
00:04:43,200 --> 00:04:46,202
Wouldn't hurt
if you had a better hometown.

69
00:04:46,287 --> 00:04:49,164
Do you mind pointing that at the floor
till I get by?

70
00:04:49,248 --> 00:04:51,749
I don't want my eye poked out.

71
00:04:51,834 --> 00:04:54,711
# But now I know your heart is shackled #

72
00:04:54,795 --> 00:04:58,256
- Don't let Billy get too far away, will you, son?
- # To a memory #

73
00:04:59,550 --> 00:05:03,052
You're a damn sight more dangerous in a
pool hall than you are on a football field.

74
00:05:03,137 --> 00:05:08,308
- # The more we drift apart #
- Hey.

75
00:05:08,392 --> 00:05:10,310
You ever heard of tackling?

76
00:05:10,394 --> 00:05:13,354
# Why can't I free your doubtful mind #

77
00:05:13,439 --> 00:05:17,901
- # And melt your cold, cold heart ##
- [Door Opens]

78
00:05:26,577 --> 00:05:28,495
- [Brakes Squealing]
- [Sonny] Hey, Duane.

79
00:05:28,579 --> 00:05:31,831
Boy, I froze my ass last night.

80
00:05:31,916 --> 00:05:35,335
Hey! Why the hell can't you kids
learn to tackle?

81
00:05:45,387 --> 00:05:50,225
Hey, how about taking Genevieve some
change, being as you're goin' that way?

82
00:05:51,435 --> 00:05:53,770
[Vehicle Approaching]

83
00:05:53,854 --> 00:05:55,772
[Horn Honks]

84
00:06:01,445 --> 00:06:04,072
[Duane]
Hike me one!

85
00:06:04,156 --> 00:06:06,324
Here comes the bomb, Crawford!

86
00:06:07,952 --> 00:06:11,329
- Look at that, Larry. They can catch.
- Feisty sons of bitches, ain't they?

87
00:06:11,413 --> 00:06:14,165
- Wish they could tackle.
- Or do something useful.

88
00:06:15,167 --> 00:06:17,585
Team wasn't worth a kiss-my-ass this year.

89
00:06:22,967 --> 00:06:24,968
- Hey, hup!
- Hup!

90
00:06:27,054 --> 00:06:30,640
- [Door Bells Jingling]
- Straight out, Crawford, one more time. Whoo-ee!

91
00:06:30,724 --> 00:06:32,350
[Bells Jingling]

92
00:06:32,893 --> 00:06:35,895
All right, you boys. Cut it out.

93
00:06:35,980 --> 00:06:39,357
I got enough problems
without you playing that game over again.

94
00:06:39,441 --> 00:06:42,569
- We could have run off to Mexico with this, you know.
- Mmm.

95
00:06:42,653 --> 00:06:45,029
[Jukebox: Man Singing, Country]
# As the door of love between us closes #

96
00:06:45,114 --> 00:06:47,323
- Hey, play that new one we heard.
- Which one?

97
00:06:47,408 --> 00:06:50,702
Down payment on breakfast.
Let somebody prosperous play the jukebox.

98
00:06:50,786 --> 00:06:54,080
- Nobody prosperous would eat here.
- [Laughing]

99
00:06:58,335 --> 00:07:02,213
- Well, I ain't very hungry.
- Well, I am.

100
00:07:02,298 --> 00:07:04,257
- Say, you want the pickup first tonight?
- Nah.

101
00:07:04,341 --> 00:07:06,926
I oughtn't get it first every Saturday night.
It's half yours, you know.

102
00:07:07,011 --> 00:07:08,386
- Go ahead.
- You sure?

103
00:07:08,512 --> 00:07:10,763
Sure, I'm sure.
Anyways, I got lots of deliveries to

104
00:07:10,764 --> 00:07:13,099
make, and I have to go clear
to Ranger this afternoon.

105
00:07:13,183 --> 00:07:16,102
- Okay.
- I'll be lucky to get back for the second show.

106
00:07:16,186 --> 00:07:19,147
# One for every time #

107
00:07:19,231 --> 00:07:22,900
# You broke my heart #

108
00:07:24,486 --> 00:07:26,404
[Clicks Tongue]

109
00:07:28,032 --> 00:07:30,366
[Man] Give me that coffee, hon?
I need another cup.

110
00:07:38,167 --> 00:07:41,336
[Radio: Man Singing, Country] # So if you
want to have fun, come along with me #

111
00:07:41,420 --> 00:07:45,131
# Say, hey, good-lookin' #

112
00:07:45,215 --> 00:07:48,468
# What ya got cookin' #

113
00:07:48,552 --> 00:07:51,804
# How's about cookin'
something up with...##

114
00:07:51,889 --> 00:07:54,057
[Crickets Chirping]

115
00:08:00,064 --> 00:08:03,608
- [Woman On Film, Chattering]
- My goodness, Sonny.

116
00:08:03,692 --> 00:08:06,069
Frank hadn't ought to
work you so late on weekends.

117
00:08:06,153 --> 00:08:07,862
That's what I keep telling him.

118
00:08:07,946 --> 00:08:11,074
You ain't got in in time
to see the comedy in three weeks.

119
00:08:11,158 --> 00:08:13,493
Hope you don't want no popcorn,
'cause there ain't none.

120
00:08:13,577 --> 00:08:16,496
- [Man On Film, Chattering]
- And you missed the newsreel too.

121
00:08:16,580 --> 00:08:20,166
And the main show's done started,
so I'll just charge you 30 cents.

122
00:08:20,250 --> 00:08:22,168
Thanks, Miss Mosey.

123
00:08:22,252 --> 00:08:24,064
[Spencer Tracy] I was
wondering if my daughter

124
00:08:24,065 --> 00:08:25,838
had deserted us, too,
when I heard her voice.

125
00:08:25,923 --> 00:08:27,799
[Elizabeth Taylor]
Pa! Pa!

126
00:08:29,093 --> 00:08:31,427
- Hi, Pa.
- [Tracy Narrating] Kay was our only daughter.

127
00:08:31,512 --> 00:08:33,846
I know a father's not supposed
to have favorites...

128
00:08:33,931 --> 00:08:35,640
but when it's Kay...

129
00:08:35,724 --> 00:08:37,684
- [Tracy] Mmm, you smell good.
- [Taylor] You like it?

130
00:08:37,768 --> 00:08:39,852
[Tracy]
Mm-hmm.

131
00:08:39,937 --> 00:08:41,854
- [Tracy] What's that?
- An atomizer.

132
00:08:41,939 --> 00:08:43,856
- Where'd you get it? A present?
- Mm-hmm.

133
00:08:43,941 --> 00:08:46,484
- Who from?
- Oh, somebody.

134
00:08:53,075 --> 00:08:54,992
I decided you had a wreck.

135
00:08:55,077 --> 00:08:56,994
[Man Coughing]

136
00:09:00,374 --> 00:09:02,875
[Tracy]
What's happened to you? You look different.

137
00:09:02,960 --> 00:09:04,961
- [Taylor] I do?
- Yeah.

138
00:09:06,171 --> 00:09:09,298
- You look all lit up inside.
- [Taylor Chuckles]

139
00:09:09,383 --> 00:09:11,467
You're not wearing
your usual deadpan look...

140
00:09:11,552 --> 00:09:14,262
that "how did I ever get
into this family" look.

141
00:09:14,346 --> 00:09:16,556
[Chuckling]
Oh, Father.

142
00:09:16,640 --> 00:09:19,225
[Tracy] Oh, I know. You've been taking
those vitamins that Dr. Gray sent you, huh?

143
00:09:19,309 --> 00:09:21,269
[Taylor]
That's right.

144
00:09:34,616 --> 00:09:36,743
[Tracy]
I guess I'll get me some of those vitamins.

145
00:09:36,827 --> 00:09:39,328
- [Phone Rings]
- [Taylor] I'll get it, Delilah.

146
00:09:40,372 --> 00:09:42,749
- [Phone Rings]
- [Taylor] What's the matter with her?

147
00:09:42,833 --> 00:09:45,001
She looks kind of queer.

148
00:09:45,085 --> 00:09:46,669
Guess what.

149
00:09:46,754 --> 00:09:48,921
What?

150
00:09:49,006 --> 00:09:51,007
It's our anniversary.

151
00:09:52,050 --> 00:09:53,551
What?

152
00:09:53,635 --> 00:09:57,096
We've been going steady a year tonight.

153
00:09:57,181 --> 00:09:59,098
Yeah?

154
00:10:00,267 --> 00:10:02,268
Seems like a lot longer.

155
00:10:03,437 --> 00:10:06,522
[Girl] You should have got me
some anniversary present.

156
00:10:06,607 --> 00:10:09,442
[Sonny] You can have another stick of gum.
That's all I got on me.

157
00:10:09,526 --> 00:10:11,068
You can give me a dollar too.

158
00:10:11,153 --> 00:10:14,071
That's how much it cost me and Marlene
for the show.

159
00:10:14,156 --> 00:10:17,408
Hi. What y'all doing
back here in the dark?

160
00:10:19,203 --> 00:10:21,454
- [Taylor] He's coming for me in a few minutes.
- [Maid] I'll get your coffee.

161
00:10:21,538 --> 00:10:23,539
[Bell Rings]

162
00:10:25,042 --> 00:10:26,793
[Tracy]
Where'd the boys go?

163
00:10:26,877 --> 00:10:30,129
[Joan Bennett] Ben had some date,
and Tommy went to basketball practice.

164
00:10:30,214 --> 00:10:32,757
- Oh, Delilah, will you bring the coffee, please?
- Yes, Mrs. Banks.

165
00:10:32,841 --> 00:10:37,470
I don't see why they should get
the pickup first all the time.

166
00:10:37,554 --> 00:10:40,473
All they ever want to do is neck anyway.

167
00:10:40,557 --> 00:10:41,974
[Man Coughing]

168
00:10:42,059 --> 00:10:44,811
[Taylor] Buckley says I'm not too young
for a man to marry.

169
00:10:44,895 --> 00:10:47,939
- [Tracy] I didn't marry your mother till I was 25.
- Oh, I know, Pop...

170
00:10:49,107 --> 00:10:51,359
[Wind Blowing]

171
00:10:52,402 --> 00:10:54,028
[Dog Barking]

172
00:10:54,112 --> 00:10:56,656
- Need some help, Jessie?
- Yeah, I sure do.

173
00:10:56,740 --> 00:10:59,158
- Hey, so long, Sam.
- Bye, Sam. Come on!

174
00:10:59,243 --> 00:11:01,661
- Good night.
- Good night, Sam. Sure did like the picture.

175
00:11:01,745 --> 00:11:04,622
- Well, good. - [Sonny] Good night.
- [Sighs] Good night.

176
00:11:08,252 --> 00:11:10,920
[Dog Barking In Distance]

177
00:11:12,047 --> 00:11:14,924
[Radio: Man Singing, Pop]
# Rose, Rose, I love you #

178
00:11:15,008 --> 00:11:17,426
# With your almond eyes #

179
00:11:17,511 --> 00:11:19,720
# Fragrant and slender#

180
00:11:19,805 --> 00:11:22,306
## [Fades]

181
00:11:22,391 --> 00:11:25,184
## [Radio: Country]

182
00:11:33,485 --> 00:11:35,903
[Dog Barking]

183
00:11:37,114 --> 00:11:39,532
[Radio: Man Singing, Pop]
# When you see the time's a-wastin' #

184
00:11:39,616 --> 00:11:42,910
- # You're a slow poke, dear #
- [Parking Brake Sets]

185
00:11:42,995 --> 00:11:44,996
# Why should I keep tryin' #

186
00:11:45,080 --> 00:11:47,081
Crack your window.
Leave the motor running.

187
00:11:47,165 --> 00:11:49,333
It's just too cold in here.

188
00:11:49,418 --> 00:11:54,839
# I guess I'll have to learn
to be a slow poke too ##

189
00:11:55,966 --> 00:11:58,551
- ## [Ends]
- [Deejay] Pee Wee King's "Slow Poke."

190
00:11:58,635 --> 00:12:00,553
Number two on the national chart.

191
00:12:00,637 --> 00:12:05,141
- Now here's a brand-new...
- [Gasps] Your hands are like ice.

192
00:12:05,225 --> 00:12:08,227
- I could put on my gloves.
- ## [Country]

193
00:12:12,316 --> 00:12:17,236
[Man]
# Send me your spoon and your napkin #

194
00:12:19,364 --> 00:12:25,077
# Send me your coffee cup too #

195
00:12:26,079 --> 00:12:29,081
What's the matter with you?
You act plain bored.

196
00:12:30,334 --> 00:12:32,501
Quit! Quit!

197
00:12:32,586 --> 00:12:36,088
- # Anything that's part of you #
- You said this was our anniversary.

198
00:12:36,173 --> 00:12:38,299
Let's do something different.

199
00:12:38,383 --> 00:12:41,636
Well, I like that. You cheapskate.

200
00:12:41,720 --> 00:12:45,514
Didn't even get me an anniversary present,
and now you wanna go and get me pregnant.

201
00:12:45,599 --> 00:12:47,600
Oh, my God, Charlene.
It was just my hand.

202
00:12:47,684 --> 00:12:49,894
Yeah. One thing leads to another.

203
00:12:49,978 --> 00:12:52,855
My mama told me how that old stuff goes.

204
00:12:52,940 --> 00:12:56,609
We'll have plenty of time for that
when we get married.

205
00:12:56,693 --> 00:12:58,653
You wasn't no livelier than me.

206
00:12:58,737 --> 00:13:03,074
That's 'cause you ain't good-lookin' enough.
You ain't even got a ducktail.

207
00:13:03,158 --> 00:13:07,453
Well, anyway, I'm done late.
Let's go on home.

208
00:13:07,537 --> 00:13:10,539
Some anniversary.
[Sighs]

209
00:13:10,624 --> 00:13:14,001
If that's the way you feel about it,
I'd just as soon break up, Charlene.

210
00:13:14,086 --> 00:13:17,880
- [Shouts] What?
- I don't want to spoil no more anniversaries for you.

211
00:13:17,965 --> 00:13:20,383
That's the way nice girls
get treated in this town.

212
00:13:20,467 --> 00:13:22,468
I might have known you wasn't dependable.

213
00:13:22,552 --> 00:13:25,137
- You wasn't even in the backfield either.
- Now, what's that got to do with it?

214
00:13:25,222 --> 00:13:28,599
This jacket's got a hole in the pocket, but
you needn't ask me to sew it up for you.

215
00:13:28,684 --> 00:13:30,643
And you give me back my pictures too.

216
00:13:30,727 --> 00:13:33,980
I don't want you showing them to all the
other boys and telling 'em how hot I am.

217
00:13:34,064 --> 00:13:36,232
- You wasn't very hot.
- [Engine Starts]

218
00:13:37,401 --> 00:13:40,403
- [Crickets Chirping]
- ## [Jukebox: Country]

219
00:13:41,989 --> 00:13:43,990
## [Continues]

220
00:14:01,425 --> 00:14:03,884
I hope you ain't down in the mouth
about Charlene.

221
00:14:03,969 --> 00:14:06,470
- I ain't blue about her.
- She don't even have a good disposition.

222
00:14:06,555 --> 00:14:08,472
What are you blue about then?

223
00:14:08,557 --> 00:14:10,641
There ain't nobody to go with in this town.

224
00:14:10,726 --> 00:14:13,894
Jacy's the only pretty girl in school,
and Duane's got her.

225
00:14:13,979 --> 00:14:15,980
I call that his tough luck.

226
00:14:17,065 --> 00:14:20,359
You don't have to eat so fast.
You ain't in a race.

227
00:14:20,444 --> 00:14:23,154
Jacy will bring him more misery
than she'll ever be worth.

228
00:14:26,616 --> 00:14:28,534
Did your dad give you this?

229
00:14:28,618 --> 00:14:30,703
- He needs all he's got.
- [Register Bell Dings]

