[Ruth Grunts]

700
00:49:30,218 --> 00:49:32,219
I'm sorry I cried.

701
00:49:33,721 --> 00:49:36,056
Just a-scared, I guess.

702
00:49:37,559 --> 00:49:40,102
Oh, he ain't gonna come.

703
00:49:40,186 --> 00:49:42,813
They're probably running plays
right now, I bet.

704
00:49:42,897 --> 00:49:44,898
No, not scared of that.

705
00:49:46,901 --> 00:49:49,403
Scared I could never do this, I guess.

706
00:49:51,656 --> 00:49:54,658
Can't seem to do anything
without crying about it.

707
00:49:57,412 --> 00:49:59,496
How could you like me?

708
00:49:59,581 --> 00:50:01,582
Oh, I like you.

709
00:50:04,252 --> 00:50:06,170
I'm glad.

710
00:50:11,384 --> 00:50:14,294
[Radio: Man Singing, Country]
# But she just wouldn't stay #

711
00:50:14,295 --> 00:50:15,679
[Billiard Balls Clattering]

712
00:50:15,763 --> 00:50:19,558
# So now that she is a-leavin' #

713
00:50:19,642 --> 00:50:22,811
# This is all I can say #

714
00:50:22,896 --> 00:50:25,981
# I got a feeling called the blues #

715
00:50:26,065 --> 00:50:29,902
# Oh, Lawd, since my baby said good-bye #

716
00:50:29,986 --> 00:50:33,906
# Lawd, I don't know what I'll do #

717
00:50:33,990 --> 00:50:37,075
# All I do is sit and cry #

718
00:50:37,160 --> 00:50:39,995
# Oh, Lawd, that last long day #

719
00:50:40,079 --> 00:50:42,915
# She said good-bye #

720
00:50:42,999 --> 00:50:46,543
# Well, Lawd, I thought I would cry#

721
00:50:46,628 --> 00:50:50,464
# She'll do me, she'll do you
She's got that kind of lovin' #

722
00:50:50,548 --> 00:50:55,802
# Lawd, I love to hear her
when she calls me Sweet Daddy ##

723
00:50:59,474 --> 00:51:03,393
[Radio: Man Singing, Country]
# So I wrote it in the words #

724
00:51:03,478 --> 00:51:07,231
# Of this song #

725
00:51:07,315 --> 00:51:09,733
# I didn't know #

726
00:51:09,817 --> 00:51:16,323
# God made honky-tonk angels #

727
00:51:16,407 --> 00:51:23,914
# I might have known
you'd never make a wife #

728
00:51:23,998 --> 00:51:28,126
# You gave up the only one #

729
00:51:28,211 --> 00:51:32,256
# That ever loved you #

730
00:51:32,340 --> 00:51:40,222
# And went back
to the wild side of life ##

731
00:51:56,114 --> 00:51:58,031
[Bell Jingling]

732
00:52:02,203 --> 00:52:05,205
Well, come on in.
I ain't gonna throw bottles at you.

733
00:52:07,083 --> 00:52:09,001
Hi.

734
00:52:09,085 --> 00:52:11,837
What have you been doing?
You lost weight.

735
00:52:11,921 --> 00:52:14,798
Ain't had any of your cheeseburgers
in weeks.

736
00:52:14,882 --> 00:52:17,676
Well, come on. I'll fix you one...

737
00:52:17,760 --> 00:52:21,305
even though that wasn't
a very nice thing y'all done to Billy.

738
00:52:21,389 --> 00:52:23,807
Can't blame Sam.

739
00:52:23,891 --> 00:52:25,517
- Was that your idea?
- No.

740
00:52:25,601 --> 00:52:26,935
- Duane's?
- Huh?

741
00:52:27,020 --> 00:52:29,646
He was there, wasn't he?

742
00:52:29,731 --> 00:52:32,232
Just didn't have the decency
to own up to it.

743
00:52:35,570 --> 00:52:38,363
Oh, don't worry.
I won't tell on him. I should though.

744
00:52:38,448 --> 00:52:40,949
- [Sizzling]
- Sure smells good.

745
00:52:41,951 --> 00:52:43,994
One thing I know for sure...

746
00:52:44,078 --> 00:52:47,456
person can't sneeze in this town without
somebody offering him a handkerchief.

747
00:52:47,540 --> 00:52:49,541
- What you mean?
- Nothin'.

748
00:52:50,710 --> 00:52:53,420
Just an awful small town
for any kind of carrying-on.

749
00:52:54,964 --> 00:52:56,965
Don't forget to put some onions on 'em.

750
00:52:58,051 --> 00:53:00,260
And some people got a lot of guns.

751
00:53:02,555 --> 00:53:04,473
[Chuckles]

752
00:53:04,557 --> 00:53:07,142
All right.
You don't need my advice anyway.

753
00:53:07,226 --> 00:53:10,687
Why don't you go play a record?
These will be done in a minute.

754
00:53:18,071 --> 00:53:20,739
[Jukebox: Drum Beating]

755
00:53:22,825 --> 00:53:24,743
- [Bells Jingling]
- [Coughing]

756
00:53:24,827 --> 00:53:28,705
[Man] # Kaw-liga was a wooden Indian
standin' by the door#

757
00:53:28,790 --> 00:53:32,209
# He fell in love with an Indian maid
over in the antique store #

758
00:53:32,293 --> 00:53:37,130
# Kaw-liga #

759
00:53:37,215 --> 00:53:40,050
# Just stood there
and never let it show #

760
00:53:40,134 --> 00:53:42,594
I just came in
to say hello to Genevieve.

761
00:53:42,678 --> 00:53:44,763
# Though she could never
answer yes or no #

762
00:53:47,850 --> 00:53:50,560
Sonny?

763
00:53:50,645 --> 00:53:52,562
Food's gettin' cold.

764
00:53:52,647 --> 00:53:55,732
# The maiden wore her beads and braids
and hoped someday he'd talk #

765
00:53:55,817 --> 00:54:00,237
# Kaw-liga #

766
00:54:00,321 --> 00:54:02,364
# Too stubborn to ever show a sign #

767
00:54:02,448 --> 00:54:04,408
What are you grinnin' about?

768
00:54:04,492 --> 00:54:07,494
Chicken-fry me a steak,
and try to use meat this time.

769
00:54:09,580 --> 00:54:13,083
# Poor old Kaw-liga
he never got a kiss #

770
00:54:13,167 --> 00:54:15,877
# Poor old Kaw-liga #

771
00:54:15,962 --> 00:54:19,214
I heard about the ball game last night.

772
00:54:19,298 --> 00:54:22,426
121 to 14.

773
00:54:22,510 --> 00:54:24,553
Must be pretty near a record.

774
00:54:24,637 --> 00:54:27,097
# That poor old wooden head #

775
00:54:27,181 --> 00:54:29,850
Sam, I'm sorry.

776
00:54:32,728 --> 00:54:35,730
I reckon y'all need glasses.

777
00:54:44,073 --> 00:54:46,575
## [Continues, Fades]

778
00:54:46,659 --> 00:54:46,700
- [Ruth] Hold still.
- [Sonny Laughs]

779
00:54:46,701 --> 00:54:49,286
- [Ruth] Hold still.
- [Sonny Laughs]

780
00:54:49,370 --> 00:54:51,788
- Want some more cookies?
[Sonny] Mm-mmm.

781
00:54:51,873 --> 00:54:54,624
- More milk?
- I'm full.

782
00:54:54,709 --> 00:54:57,711
## [Ruth Humming]

783
00:55:04,469 --> 00:55:07,053
Hey, how come you've stayed
with the coach?

784
00:55:07,138 --> 00:55:09,055
You don't like him much.

785
00:55:09,140 --> 00:55:11,641
Oh, I weren't brought up
to leave a husband.

786
00:55:11,726 --> 00:55:13,977
I guess that's why.

787
00:55:14,061 --> 00:55:16,062
Maybe I was just scared to.

788
00:55:17,231 --> 00:55:20,233
I never noticed how ugly this room is.

789
00:55:20,318 --> 00:55:23,695
- What's your favorite color?
- Oh, I don't know. Blue.

790
00:55:23,779 --> 00:55:26,656
- Maybe I'll repaper it.
- Well, why'd you marry him?

791
00:55:26,741 --> 00:55:29,326
I don't know.
My mother didn't like him.

792
00:55:29,410 --> 00:55:31,661
Maybe that was it.
[Chuckling]

793
00:55:31,746 --> 00:55:33,747
But I was 20 years old.

794
00:55:33,831 --> 00:55:37,167
I thought hairy-chested football coaches
were about it.

795
00:55:38,169 --> 00:55:41,087
I'm gonna buy us a new quilt.

796
00:55:41,172 --> 00:55:43,798
A blue one.

797
00:55:43,883 --> 00:55:46,551
What do you think he'd do
if he found us?

798
00:55:46,636 --> 00:55:49,012
Shoot us probably.

799
00:55:49,096 --> 00:55:52,098
He's always glad to have an excuse
to use his deer rifle.

800
00:55:57,355 --> 00:56:00,690
[Bird Calling]

801
00:56:09,116 --> 00:56:11,910
I thought you boys wanted to fish.

802
00:56:11,994 --> 00:56:14,621
Come on.
Keep an eye on them corks, Billy.

803
00:56:20,586 --> 00:56:23,630
I don't think there's anything
in this tank 'cept turtles.

804
00:56:23,714 --> 00:56:26,550
That's what I like about it,
tell you the truth.

805
00:56:26,634 --> 00:56:28,635
- Want to try one?
- Sure.

806
00:56:32,265 --> 00:56:35,058
I never liked to clean fish
or eat them either.

807
00:56:35,142 --> 00:56:37,686
Spend half your time picking out bones.

808
00:56:40,565 --> 00:56:43,275
Yeah, I just come out here
to get a little scenery.

809
00:56:43,359 --> 00:56:45,819
Too pretty a day to spend in town.

810
00:56:49,949 --> 00:56:52,450
You wouldn't believe
how this country's changed.

811
00:56:56,330 --> 00:56:59,833
First time I seen it,
there wasn't a mesquite tree on it...

812
00:56:59,917 --> 00:57:02,460
or a prickly pear neither.

813
00:57:02,545 --> 00:57:04,879
I used to own this land, you know.

814
00:57:06,257 --> 00:57:10,594
First time I watered a horse at this tank
was more than 40 years ago.

815
00:57:13,014 --> 00:57:15,515
I reckon the reason
why I always drag you out here...

816
00:57:15,600 --> 00:57:19,603
is probably I'm just as sentimental as the
next fella when it comes to old times.

817
00:57:24,859 --> 00:57:27,152
Old times.

818
00:57:27,236 --> 00:57:30,405
I brought a young lady
swimming out here once.

819
00:57:30,489 --> 00:57:32,657
More than 20 years ago.

820
00:57:35,536 --> 00:57:39,873
It was after my wife had lost her mind
and my boys was dead.

821
00:57:43,961 --> 00:57:47,213
Me and this young lady
was pretty wild, I guess.

822
00:57:48,716 --> 00:57:50,675
In pretty deep.

823
00:57:53,346 --> 00:57:57,140
We used to come out here a-horseback
and go swimmin' without no bathin' suits.

824
00:57:57,224 --> 00:57:59,142
[Chuckles]

825
00:58:00,728 --> 00:58:04,731
One day, she wanted
to swim the horses across this tank.

826
00:58:04,815 --> 00:58:07,817
Kind of a crazy thing to do,
but we done it anyway.

827
00:58:09,153 --> 00:58:12,238
She bet me a silver dollar
she could beat me across.

828
00:58:13,324 --> 00:58:15,241
She did.

829
00:58:16,410 --> 00:58:19,871
This old horse I was a-ridin'
didn't want to take the water.

830
00:58:19,955 --> 00:58:23,291
But she was always lookin'
for somethin' to do like that.

831
00:58:24,794 --> 00:58:26,753
Somethin' wild.

832
00:58:28,631 --> 00:58:31,341
I'll bet she's still got
that silver dollar.

833
00:58:33,260 --> 00:58:35,845
- [Chuckles]
- Whatever happened to her?

834
00:58:37,640 --> 00:58:40,308
Oh, she growed up.

835
00:58:40,393 --> 00:58:42,727
She was just a girl then really.

836
00:58:45,147 --> 00:58:47,315
Here, let me help you with that.

837
00:58:48,317 --> 00:58:50,819
Why didn't you ever marry her
after your wife died?

838
00:58:53,572 --> 00:58:55,573
She was already married.

839
00:59:00,955 --> 00:59:03,707
Her and her husband was young
and miserable with one another...

840
00:59:03,791 --> 00:59:06,334
like so many young married folks are.

841
00:59:07,336 --> 00:59:11,297
I thought they'd change with some age, but...
didn't turn out that way.

842
00:59:12,550 --> 00:59:14,551
[Sonny]
ls being married always so miserable?

843
00:59:14,635 --> 00:59:17,887
No, not really.
About 80% of the time, I guess.

844
00:59:20,975 --> 00:59:24,519
We ought to go
to a real fishing tank next year.

845
00:59:24,603 --> 00:59:27,564
Nah, it don't do to think about
things like that too much.

846
00:59:29,984 --> 00:59:33,403
If she was here, I'd probably be
just as crazy now as I was then...

847
00:59:33,487 --> 00:59:35,447
in about five minutes.

848
00:59:36,449 --> 00:59:38,450
Ain't that ridiculous?

849
00:59:40,494 --> 00:59:42,704
No, it ain't really...

850
00:59:42,788 --> 00:59:47,584
'cause being crazy about a woman like her
is always the right thing to do.

851
00:59:47,668 --> 00:59:50,587
[Chuckles]
Being a decrepit old bag of bones...

852
00:59:50,671 --> 00:59:52,922
that's what's ridiculous.

853
00:59:53,007 --> 00:59:54,924
Gettin' old.

854
00:59:59,513 --> 01:00:01,639
[Exhales]

855
01:00:01,724 --> 01:00:02,640
## [Background: Ballad]

856
01:00:02,641 --> 01:00:05,059
## [Background: Ballad]

857
01:00:05,144 --> 01:00:08,938
[Man]
# Talk to her, please #

858
01:00:09,023 --> 01:00:11,441
# Mr. Sun #

859
01:00:13,068 --> 01:00:15,945
# Speak to her #

860
01:00:16,030 --> 01:00:19,365
# Mr. Rainbow #

861
01:00:20,367 --> 01:00:27,332
# And take her under your branches #

862
01:00:27,416 --> 01:00:31,669
# Mr. Tree #

863
01:00:35,883 --> 01:00:39,177
# Whisper to her#

864
01:00:39,261 --> 01:00:41,930
# Mr. Wind #

865
01:00:43,474 --> 01:00:46,684
# Sing to her #

866
01:00:46,769 --> 01:00:49,020
- # Mr. Robin #
- My God, I'm glad it wasn't on fire.

867
01:00:49,104 --> 01:00:52,440
I would have burned to death
before you got one button undone.

868
01:00:52,525 --> 01:00:54,484
I'm going to get a drink of water.

869
01:00:54,568 --> 01:01:00,365
# Mr. Moonlight
put in a word for me ##

870
01:01:00,449 --> 01:01:02,242
Hi.

871
01:01:02,326 --> 01:01:05,954
I wondered where you went.
Annie Annie asleep?

872
01:01:06,038 --> 01:01:07,956
Yeah.

873
01:01:13,087 --> 01:01:15,046
[Exhales]

874
01:01:22,596 --> 01:01:24,514
Nice. You a virgin?

875
01:01:26,392 --> 01:01:27,934
Guess I am.

876
01:01:29,061 --> 01:01:31,396
Too bad.

877
01:01:31,480 --> 01:01:34,524
- I don't want to be though.
- I don't blame you.

878
01:01:34,608 --> 01:01:36,985
Come see me when you're not.

879
01:01:41,156 --> 01:01:45,201
[Jukebox: Man Singing, Country]
# Another love before my time #

880
01:01:45,286 --> 01:01:49,247
# Made your heart sad and blue #

881
01:01:49,331 --> 01:01:53,543
# And so my heart is paying now#

882
01:01:53,627 --> 01:01:57,338
# For things I didn't do #

883
01:01:57,423 --> 01:02:01,718
- # In anger, unkind words are said #
- [Slurping]

884
01:02:01,802 --> 01:02:05,555
Why don't we just take off and go someplace?
I'm sick and tired of this town.

885
01:02:05,639 --> 01:02:08,057
- You're the only friend I got here.
- You mean go and stay gone?

886
01:02:08,142 --> 01:02:10,059
Except Jacy. No, I don't know.

887
01:02:11,437 --> 01:02:14,439
Hey, we could go to Mexico.
Be back sometime Monday.

888
01:02:14,523 --> 01:02:17,317
- You reckon the pickup would make it?
- It might. How much money you got?

889
01:02:17,401 --> 01:02:19,319
Oh, 30 bucks about.

890
01:02:19,403 --> 01:02:21,946
Well, I got 40.
We could make a run with that. Come on!

891
01:02:22,031 --> 01:02:24,198
Okay.

892
01:02:24,283 --> 01:02:28,244
- You boys want... Hey, where you going?
- Mexico.

893
01:02:28,329 --> 01:02:29,245
Where?

894
01:02:29,330 --> 01:02:31,247
[Engine Revving]

895
01:02:31,332 --> 01:02:33,791
[Radio: Man Singing, Country]
# ...more of your kisses #

896
01:02:33,876 --> 01:02:37,003
- # I want more, more, more tender kisses #
- Better come with us, Sam.

897
01:02:37,087 --> 01:02:39,005
We're headed for the valley.

898
01:02:39,089 --> 01:02:41,591
- Going where, did you say?
- [Sonny] Mexico.

899
01:02:41,675 --> 01:02:44,093
- I hear it's about the wildest.
- Yeah, all the way down.

900
01:02:44,178 --> 01:02:48,181
You're going all the way to Mexico tonight
in this old heap of junk?

901
01:02:48,265 --> 01:02:50,183
- [Duane Chuckling]
- My God.

902
01:02:50,267 --> 01:02:52,602
Reckon the town
get along without us till Monday?

903
01:02:52,686 --> 01:02:54,604
Oh, I reckon.

904
01:02:54,688 --> 01:02:57,941
If I was young enough to bounce that far,
I'd go with you.

905
01:02:58,025 --> 01:03:00,944
- Need any money?
- No, we got plenty.

906
01:03:01,028 --> 01:03:04,364
Well, you'd better take some
for some insurance.

907
01:03:05,366 --> 01:03:08,576
Take money below that border,
it sort of melts sometimes.

908
01:03:08,661 --> 01:03:10,787
Well, thanks, Sam.

909
01:03:10,871 --> 01:03:13,247
And try not to drink too much
of that buggy water.

910
01:03:13,332 --> 01:03:17,293
Oh, we'll just drink beer and tequila.

911
01:03:17,378 --> 01:03:20,171
Yeah. You catch the clap,
you'll wish you hadn't drunk nothin'.

912
01:03:20,255 --> 01:03:21,965
[Sonny, Duane Laughing]

913
01:03:22,049 --> 01:03:26,386
# I want more, more, more tender kisses #

914
01:03:26,470 --> 01:03:30,598
# The neighbors all raise Cain
and I know that it's a shame #

915
01:03:30,683 --> 01:03:33,643
# But I've got to have
another tender kiss ##

916
01:03:33,727 --> 01:03:36,896
Oh, well. We'll see you.

917
01:03:36,981 --> 01:03:38,982
- [Duane] Adios!
- So long!

918
01:03:55,332 --> 01:03:59,877
[Radio: Man Singing, Country] # Well, I'm
in love, I'm in love with a beautiful gal #

919
01:03:59,962 --> 01:04:03,131
# That's what's the matter with me #

920
01:04:03,215 --> 01:04:06,426
# Well, I'm in love
I'm in love with a beautiful gal #

921
01:04:06,510 --> 01:04:08,970
# But she don't care about me #

922
01:04:09,054 --> 01:04:12,015
Duane. Hey, wake up.

923
01:04:12,099 --> 01:04:14,100
We're back.

924
01:04:15,227 --> 01:04:18,229
Oh, my stomach don't feel so good.
Got any more of those TUMS?

925
01:04:18,313 --> 01:04:22,233
Aw, you ate 'em all
before we got to San Antone.

926
01:04:23,277 --> 01:04:26,446
Well, Genevieve will have something.
My stomach, it don't feel so good.

927
01:04:29,324 --> 01:04:30,825
[Sonny]
Closed.

928
01:04:30,909 --> 01:04:33,244
Closed?

929
01:04:33,328 --> 01:04:34,829
Yeah.

930
01:04:34,913 --> 01:04:37,165
I never seen it closed before.

931
01:04:37,249 --> 01:04:39,250
No, not even for Christmas.

932
01:04:40,836 --> 01:04:43,755
Maybe Sam will have something.
'Cause I'm sick.

933
01:04:46,675 --> 01:04:48,968
[Groans]

934
01:04:54,349 --> 01:04:56,309
- ## [Stops]
- [Engine Stops]

935
01:05:06,945 --> 01:05:09,113
[Sonny]
Oh, it ain't that early.

936
01:05:09,198 --> 01:05:10,948
Must be some kind of holiday.

937
01:05:11,033 --> 01:05:13,826
Sam don't close on holidays.

938
01:05:13,911 --> 01:05:15,828
Maybe he had to go someplace.

939
01:05:19,792 --> 01:05:22,335
- Well, let's go ask Andy, huh?
