till we find out somethin'.

1396
01:39:27,420 --> 01:39:29,296
I don't know what your rights are.

1397
01:39:29,381 --> 01:39:31,215
I guess we better follow him, honey.

1398
01:39:31,299 --> 01:39:33,968
I'll just be heartbroken
if my folks have done this.

1399
01:39:34,052 --> 01:39:36,637
## [Continues, Indistinct]

1400
01:39:39,307 --> 01:39:42,476
You think I worked like a dog all my life
so my daughter can end up in a pool hall?

1401
01:39:42,561 --> 01:39:44,270
We was gonna get another apartment.

1402
01:39:44,354 --> 01:39:46,772
I'll bet you was.
Where are your car keys, hon?

1403
01:39:46,857 --> 01:39:49,108
It's a hell of a note. A hell of a note.
Just a hell of a note!

1404
01:39:49,192 --> 01:39:51,318
- Oh, shut up and take her home.
- You bet I will!

1405
01:39:51,403 --> 01:39:53,154
- I'm tired of this.
- You take her car.

1406
01:39:53,238 --> 01:39:55,239
As far as I'm concerned,
he can walk!

1407
01:40:02,747 --> 01:40:05,833
- [Car Door Slams]
- [Engine Starts]

1408
01:40:11,256 --> 01:40:13,966
[Engine Revs]

1409
01:40:24,436 --> 01:40:26,353
Not much of a wedding night, huh?

1410
01:40:26,438 --> 01:40:28,772
Nope, not much of one.

1411
01:40:28,857 --> 01:40:32,359
Here, have a little drink of bourbon.
It'll pick you up.

1412
01:40:32,444 --> 01:40:34,403
Take all of it. I'm gonna drive.

1413
01:40:37,115 --> 01:40:42,119
You won't believe this, Sonny, but you're lucky
we got you clear of her quick as we did.

1414
01:40:42,204 --> 01:40:45,289
You'd have been a lot better off
staying with Ruth Popper.

1415
01:40:45,373 --> 01:40:47,374
Does everybody know about that?

1416
01:40:47,459 --> 01:40:49,668
[Chuckles]
Of course.

1417
01:40:49,753 --> 01:40:52,046
Sounded like a good deal to me, kiddo.

1418
01:40:52,130 --> 01:40:54,256
You shouldn't have let
Jacy turn your head.

1419
01:40:54,341 --> 01:40:57,176
Well, she's prettier.

1420
01:40:57,260 --> 01:40:59,762
I guess I shouldn't have though.

1421
01:40:59,846 --> 01:41:03,140
- I guess I treated her terrible.
- Guess you did.

1422
01:41:09,397 --> 01:41:12,650
- [Dogs Barking In Distance]
- ## [Radio: Country]

1423
01:41:21,117 --> 01:41:22,910
## [Stops]

1424
01:41:22,994 --> 01:41:25,079
Sure weren't out of Texas very long.

1425
01:41:25,163 --> 01:41:27,998
Well, Oklahoma's not much
of an improvement.

1426
01:41:33,797 --> 01:41:35,798
It's not the same now.

1427
01:41:37,509 --> 01:41:40,594
Nothing's really been right
since Sam the Lion died.

1428
01:41:43,515 --> 01:41:45,015
No.

1429
01:41:46,184 --> 01:41:47,893
No, it hasn't.

1430
01:41:51,856 --> 01:41:53,357
Oh, God.

1431
01:41:56,319 --> 01:41:58,696
I get sad if I think of Sam for long.

1432
01:42:02,826 --> 01:42:04,994
Did you know he had beautiful hands?

1433
01:42:06,871 --> 01:42:08,831
I guess you liked him, didn't you?

1434
01:42:10,208 --> 01:42:12,334
I guess everybody did.

1435
01:42:14,504 --> 01:42:17,965
Well, I'll tell you.
It was different with me, Sonny.

1436
01:42:18,049 --> 01:42:20,009
I loved him.

1437
01:42:21,052 --> 01:42:23,053
He loved me too.

1438
01:42:26,474 --> 01:42:28,684
Are you... [Chuckles]

1439
01:42:28,768 --> 01:42:32,521
Are you the one he used
to take swimmin' out in the tank?

1440
01:42:32,605 --> 01:42:34,356
He told you about that, huh?

1441
01:42:35,900 --> 01:42:37,609
Yeah, I was the one.

1442
01:42:39,195 --> 01:42:41,155
[Exhales]

1443
01:42:41,239 --> 01:42:45,993
I guess if it wasn't for Sam, I'd...
[Sniffles] just about have missed it...

1444
01:42:46,077 --> 01:42:47,995
whatever it is.

1445
01:42:49,414 --> 01:42:52,833
I'd have been one of them Amity types
that thinks that...

1446
01:42:52,917 --> 01:42:57,171
playin' bridge is about
the best thing that life has to offer.

1447
01:42:57,255 --> 01:42:59,256
[Chuckles]

1448
01:43:03,803 --> 01:43:06,180
[Sighs]
Old Sam the Lion.

1449
01:43:09,267 --> 01:43:11,977
"Sam the Lion." You know,
nobody knows where he got that name.

1450
01:43:12,062 --> 01:43:14,188
I gave it to him.

1451
01:43:14,272 --> 01:43:18,192
One night, oh, it just came to me.

1452
01:43:20,862 --> 01:43:24,031
He... He was so pleased.

1453
01:43:28,119 --> 01:43:30,120
I was 22 years old then.

1454
01:43:31,915 --> 01:43:34,041
Can you imagine?

1455
01:43:36,044 --> 01:43:38,879
[Laughs]
I'll tell you, Sonny...

1456
01:43:38,963 --> 01:43:42,466
it's terrible to only meet one man in your
whole life who knows what you're worth.

1457
01:43:44,302 --> 01:43:45,803
Just terrible.

1458
01:43:48,890 --> 01:43:50,891
I've looked too.

1459
01:43:52,352 --> 01:43:54,812
You wouldn't believe
how I've looked.

1460
01:43:59,484 --> 01:44:03,862
- Well, now I know why Sam liked you.
- Loved me!

1461
01:44:03,947 --> 01:44:05,823
Loved you, I mean.

1462
01:44:05,907 --> 01:44:09,410
Do you?

1463
01:44:09,494 --> 01:44:11,662
Well, I can kind of see
what he saw in you too.

1464
01:44:21,673 --> 01:44:23,966
Nope, I'll just go on home.

1465
01:44:24,050 --> 01:44:25,551
- Go on, get out.
- [Engine Starts]

1466
01:44:25,635 --> 01:44:30,222
# I got a feeling called the blues
Oh, Lawd #

1467
01:44:30,306 --> 01:44:33,183
Think I could...
think I could learn to drink?

1468
01:44:33,268 --> 01:44:37,354
# Lawd, I don't know what I'll do #

1469
01:44:37,439 --> 01:44:39,731
[Laughing]

1470
01:44:39,816 --> 01:44:42,443
You might.
You better keep on practicing.

