## [Soundtrack]

1532
01:49:19,804 --> 01:49:22,139
- ## [Ends]
- [Projector Whirs To Stop]

1533
01:49:27,061 --> 01:49:31,815
- That was a good movie.
- Yeah, I seen it here before once.

1534
01:49:31,899 --> 01:49:34,651
Why don't we run over to Wichita
and drink a little beer, huh?

1535
01:49:34,736 --> 01:49:37,237
Okay. I got lots of time till morning.

1536
01:49:37,321 --> 01:49:38,822
Sure.

1537
01:49:40,491 --> 01:49:43,326
- [Sonny] Well, so long, Miss Mosey.
- Sorry you're closing the show.

1538
01:49:43,411 --> 01:49:46,079
Nobody wants to come
to shows no more.

1539
01:49:46,164 --> 01:49:48,039
Kid baseball in the summer...

1540
01:49:48,124 --> 01:49:50,041
television all the time.

1541
01:49:51,711 --> 01:49:54,838
If Sam had lived, I...
l believe we could have kept it goin'.

1542
01:49:54,922 --> 01:49:58,258
But I just didn't have the know-how.

1543
01:49:59,343 --> 01:50:01,386
Won't be much to do in town
with the picture show closed.

1544
01:50:01,471 --> 01:50:02,637
Yeah.

1545
01:50:05,099 --> 01:50:07,100
Well, so long.

1546
01:50:07,185 --> 01:50:08,518
Duane.

1547
01:50:09,687 --> 01:50:11,855
You watch out now overseas.

1548
01:50:19,614 --> 01:50:24,868
[Radio: Man Singing, Country]
# Each night I laid there in prison #

1549
01:50:26,454 --> 01:50:32,167
# I pictured a future so bright #

1550
01:50:34,712 --> 01:50:36,713
Sure weren't no women around.

1551
01:50:39,884 --> 01:50:42,886
I guess the next piece of ass I get
will be yellow.

1552
01:50:42,970 --> 01:50:45,430
Wished I was going with you.

1553
01:50:47,725 --> 01:50:49,768
Hey, why don't you take care
of the car for me?

1554
01:50:49,852 --> 01:50:51,770
What, your ma don't need it?

1555
01:50:51,854 --> 01:50:55,065
I wouldn't want her driving it,
no better than she can drive.

1556
01:50:55,149 --> 01:50:57,484
You might help her take the groceries home,
you got the time.

1557
01:50:57,568 --> 01:50:59,069
Okay.

1558
01:50:59,153 --> 01:51:01,321
[Bus Brakes Squeal]

1559
01:51:01,405 --> 01:51:04,574
[Bus Engine Idling]

1560
01:51:04,659 --> 01:51:06,326
[Car Door Closes]

1561
01:51:06,410 --> 01:51:08,537
[Shivers]

1562
01:51:11,332 --> 01:51:14,501
You ever, uh... You ever hear from Jacy?

1563
01:51:14,585 --> 01:51:17,212
No, not a thing.

1564
01:51:17,296 --> 01:51:21,550
She don't get home much.
Ain't been back to town since August.

1565
01:51:21,634 --> 01:51:23,677
I guess she just stays
in Dallas all the time.

1566
01:51:23,761 --> 01:51:25,762
Yeah, probably does.

1567
